This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with vehicle recognition from a single RGB image using 2D and 3D bounding boxes. The paper also involves the use of deep learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel 3D perspective network, which involves geometric constraints, indicating that it could also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Finally, the paper presents qualitative and quantitative results, suggesting that it could also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
